article.description: — Damion Squire posted 19 points as Portland State narrowly beat Northern Arizona 68-67 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Squire leads Portland St. past N. Arizona 68-67
article.linkText: Squire leads Portland St. past N. Arizona 68-67
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. -- — Damion Squire posted 19 points as Portland State narrowly beat Northern Arizona 68-67 on Thursday night. Khalid Thomas had 15 points for Portland State (9-15, 7-9 Big Sky Conference). Michael Carter III added 14 points. Ezekiel Alley had 13 points. Jalen Cone had 19 points for the Lumberjacks (9-17, 5-10). He also had eight turnovers but only two assists. Keith Haymon added 13 points and eight rebounds. Jay Green had 11 points. The Vikings improve to 2-0 against the Lumberjacks this season. Portland State defeated Northern Arizona 97-76 on Jan. 29. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
